But then you need to implement ICommand, etc. The Click event works well enough. 

You could also handle MouseLeftButtonDown on the Rectangle itself. You&#39;d still have to set its Fill to Transparent. I prefer this solution because Click behavior is more complicated than MouseLeftButtonDown: For example, when you mouse down on 
a button and drag out of the button before releasing the mouse button, Click isn&#39;t raised. Users are accustomed to that behavior.

